## 2. Prerrequisitos

### Versiones minimas

| Componente | Version minima | Verificar | Instalar |
|---|---|---|---|
| **Node.js** | 18.0.0 | `node --version` | `sudo apt install -y nodejs` |
| **npm** | 9.0.0 | `npm --version` | `sudo apt install -y npm` |
| **Python 3** | 3.10 | `python3 --version` | `sudo apt install -y python3` |
| **PyYAML** | 6.0 | `python3 -c "import yaml; print(yaml.__version__)"` | `pip3 install --user pyyaml` |
| **jsonschema** | 4.0 | `python3 -c "import jsonschema; print(jsonschema.__version__)"` | `pip3 install --user jsonschema` |
| **curl** | cualquiera | `curl --version` | `sudo apt install -y curl` |
| **git** | cualquiera | `git --version` | `sudo apt install -y git` |
| **opencode-ai** (opcional, v2.9.0) | 1.0+ | `opencode --version` | `npm install -g opencode-ai` |

### Dependencias opcionales (recomendadas)

Estas herramientas activan analizadores especificos. Sin ellas, el sistema degrada gracefulmente con regex fallback.

| Herramienta | Para que | Instalar |
|---|---|---|
| **bandit** | Analisis de seguridad Python | `pip3 install --user bandit` |
| **radon** | Complejidad ciclomatica Python | `pip3 install --user radon` |
| **coverage** + **pytest** | Coverage de tests Python | `pip3 install --user coverage pytest` |
| **safety** | CVE scan Python | `pip3 install --user safety` |
| **pip-audit** | CVE scan Python (alternativa) | `pip3 install --user pip-audit` |
| **gosec** | Analisis de seguridad Go | `go install github.com/securego/gosec/cmd/gosec@latest` |
| **gocyclo** | Complejidad ciclomatica Go | `go install github.com/fzipp/gocyclo/cmd/gocyclo@latest` |
| **govulncheck** | CVE scan Go | `go install golang.org/x/vuln/cmd/govulncheck@latest` |
| **cppcheck** | Analisis C/C++ | `sudo apt install -y cppcheck` |
| **cargo-audit** | CVE scan Rust | `cargo install cargo-audit` |
| **typescript-language-server** | LSP TypeScript | `npm install -g typescript-language-server typescript` |
| **pyright** | LSP Python | `npm install -g pyright` |
| **@playwright/mcp** | Captura visual (panel MCP) | ya en opencode.json |
| **opencode-fastedit** | Edicion rapida (MCP) | ya en opencode.json |

### Verificar prerequisitos en un comando

```bash
echo "Node: $(node --version 2>/dev/null || echo FALTA)"
echo "npm:  $(npm --version 2>/dev/null || echo FALTA)"
echo "Py:   $(python3 --version 2>/dev/null || echo FALTA)"
echo "PyYAML: $(python3 -c 'import yaml; print(yaml.__version__)' 2>/dev/null || echo FALTA)"
echo "jsonschema: $(python3 -c 'import jsonschema; print(jsonschema.__version__)' 2>/dev/null || echo FALTA)"
echo "curl: $(curl --version 2>/dev/null | head -1 || echo FALTA)"
echo "git:  $(git --version 2>/dev/null || echo FALTA)"
echo "opencode: $(opencode --version 2>/dev/null || echo 'no instalado (opcional)')"
```

